.TH "vmw_stdu_bind_st" 9 "vmw_stdu_bind_st" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_stdu_bind_st \- Binds a surface to a Screen Target
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_stdu_bind_st
.BI "(struct vmw_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_screen_target_display_unit *stdu "  ","
.BI "const struct vmw_resource *res "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
VMW DRM device
.IP "stdu" 12
display unit affected
.IP "res" 12
Buffer to bind to the screen target.  Set to NULL to blank screen.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Binding a surface to a Screen Target the same as flipping
